<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1437,217,566]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
Diagnosis (after 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[337,463,217,242]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974">
Cook 
<number box="[404,463,217,241]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" value="1974.0">1974</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, revised): Characters of subfamily Axonopsinae. Dorsal shield complete, with a pair of distinct or indistinct posterolateral indentations. Suture lines of coxae either distinct or obliterated. Genital field with three pairs of acetabula, fused with ventral shield in males but on separate plates in female. A distinct ridge present anterolaterally from insertion of fourth legs. Opening for insertion of fourth legs without apparent condyles or projections. Posterolateral suture lines of fourth coxae may be complete or completely absent. Excretory pore lying on a distinct tubercle. Palp without projections or heavy ventral setae. Legs without sexual dimorphism; distal segments of first leg with a reduced setation, first leg longer than second leg.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1437,217,566]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
Species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[456,529,470,493]" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Ljania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[456,529,470,493]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Ljania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reported from Europe, 
<collectingCountry box="[860,927,470,493]" name="Japan" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Japan</collectingCountry>
, Russian Far East, 
<collectingCountry box="[1160,1305,469,494]" name="South Korea" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">South Korea</collectingCountry>
and North 
<collectingCountry box="[151,247,505,530]" name="United States of America" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">America</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Imamura" box="[261,429,505,530]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refString="Imamura, T. (1956) Some subterranean water-mites from Hyogo Prefecture, Japan. Comte Rendu Premier Congres International de Speleologie, 3 (3), 193 - 214." type="journal article" year="1956">
Imamura 
<number box="[370,429,505,530]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" value="1956.0">1956</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[439,566,505,530]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974">
Cook 
<number box="[507,566,505,529]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" value="1974.0">1974</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kim" box="[576,800,505,530]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refString="Kim, I. - H. &amp; Chung, K. - S. (1996) Water mites of Axonopsinae (Acarina, Aturidae) from Korea. The Korean Journal of Systematic Zoology, 12, 137 - 165." type="journal article" year="1996">
Kim &amp; Chung 
<number box="[741,800,505,530]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tuzovskij" box="[810,989,505,530]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refString="Tuzovskij, P. V. (2012) Water mites of the genus Ljania Thor, 1898 (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Aturidae) in Russia. Zootaxa, 3249, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="2012">
Tuzovskij 
<number box="[928,989,505,529]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The records presented in this paper are the first from the Oriental region, and require an emendation of the genus as given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[1114,1259,541,566]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974">
Cook (
<number box="[1190,1251,542,566]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" value="1974.0">1974</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
